38
00:02:15,969 --> 00:02:19,401
shifted in phase. Together, they form a complex wave that

39
00:02:19,501 --> 00:02:23,677
propagates through space. This wave-like nature is what gives quantum

40
00:02:23,777 --> 00:02:27,023
mechanics its strange and counterintuitive properties.

41
00:02:28,118 --> 00:02:31,587
Let's break down each term in the Schrödinger equation

42
00:02:31,687 --> 00:02:35,486
to understand what it represents physically. First, we have

43
00:02:35,586 --> 00:02:38,394
i times h-bar, where i is the imaginary unit

44
00:02:38,494 --> 00:02:42,029
and h-bar is the reduced Planck constant. This constant

45
00:02:42,129 --> 00:02:46,721
connects the microscopic quantum world to our macroscopic measurements.

46
00:02:46,821 --> 00:02:50,055
The time derivative term tells us how the wave function

47
00:02:50,155 --> 00:02:52,964
changes from one moment to the next. This is the

48
00:02:53,064 --> 00:02:57,206
dynamic part of quantum mechanics. The partial derivative with respect

49
00:02:57,306 --> 00:03:00,357
to time captures the evolution of the quantum state.

50
00:03:00,457 --> 00:03:04,071
The kinetic energy term contains the second spatial derivative of

51
00:03:04,171 --> 00:03:07,499
the wave function. This term describes how the wave function

52
00:03:07,599 --> 00:03:10,985
curves in space. A highly curved wave function corresponds to

53
